# Core Business Logic Module

## PURPOSE
Platform-agnostic core functionality that doesn't depend on specific email providers or browser APIs.
Contains reusable logic for scanning, authentication, and data management.

## CONTAINS
- scanner.js: Abstract email scanning orchestrator
- auth.js: Authentication state management
- storage.js: StorageAdapter interface (platform-neutral contract; browser-specific implementations injected at runtime)
- subscription.js: Subscription data models and utilities

## RESPONSIBILITIES
- Coordinate email scanning across different providers
- Manage authentication tokens and user sessions
- Handle local data persistence
- Parse and normalize subscription data
- Enforce business rules (free tier limits, deduplication)

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /src/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Uses: /src/providers/* for provider-specific implementations

## RULES
- Must not contain provider-specific code
- Domain logic must be pure and testable; side effects (auth, storage, I/O) isolated in boundary adapters (AuthAdapter, StorageService, SessionStore) injected via dependency injection
- Use dependency injection for provider implementations and adapters
- Handle errors gracefully with meaningful messages in adapter boundaries
- Adapters must implement explicit interfaces for testability
